# Git Push Protocol

1. Run `git status` and `git diff --stat` to see what changed
2. Draft a concise commit message from the diff (1-line summary + optional body)
3. Run: `git add -A && git commit -m "<message>" && git push origin main`
4. Report the commit hash and files changed
